VMusical weekend
p3
sVnews
p4
VBangalore Sangeet Sabha is organising a Hindustani classical vocal concert by Vyasamurti Katti, a disciple of Indudhar Nirodhi of Mysore. He will be accompanied on the tabla by Keshava Joshi and the harmonium by Sukhada Limaye Joshi. The programme starts at 6.30 p.m. on December 19 and 20. It will be held at Seva Sadan, 14th cross, East Park Road, Malleswaram. Entry is free.  For more information, contact 23345908,9845349112.The sixth anniversary celebrations of the Nadabrahma Kurudi Venkannachar Trust will be held at Green Arch, Hotel Woodlands, Rajarammohan Roy Road from 4.20 p.m. onwards on December 21.A felicitation function on the 81st birthday celebrations of Vidwan Venkannachar Kurudi will also be held. Sangeeta Vidwan and renowned flautist K.C. Ashwathanarayana and Sangeeta Vidhushi and veena artist Santhi Rao will be felicitated at the function.Dr. Vijayalakshmi Balekundri, professor of paediatric cardiology, Sri Jayadeva institute of Cardiology will be the chief guest at the event.The invocation address and the welcome speech by Bhadragari Sarvothama Das will start the proceedings, followed by the inauguration of the event and felicitation ceremony of the dignitaries. A set of scholarships will also be awarded to musicians such as E. Shankar, Kumari Mangala D. and Veerabhadra Swami, who are talented students from the Karnataka Welfare Association of the Blind.A CD OF kabir bhajans sung by K.V. Nandakumar will also be released. After the vote of thanks, some cultural programmes involving Hndustani and Carnatic classical music will be held.
